@Node Require "Requirements"

@{u}Requirements@{uu}

The game is planned for AGA only. It might be possible for me to make an ESC version
as well but while I'm developing it, the AGA mode will be used only.

You will need about 800k of free chipram.
You will need about 1 Meg of extra ram on top of this.

Last time I tested it, it used 700k of Chipram and 600k of fast ram. As you can
imagine, as soon as I add the extra graphics, samples, plenty of extra code
it will then be pushed to work on anything less than 1Meg Chip.

You will need all the speed you can get!!!

My own personal Amiga is just a basic A1200 020/14 with an extra 4Meg of fast. This
setup will probably be the minimum requirements for the finished game. I will try
and keep it playable on an 020/14 but any extra speed will make the game run much
better. Of course, any extra fast ram will also help.

@EndNode


#############################


@Node faq "Frequently asked Questions"

@{u}The usual questions@{uu}

I knew I'd get some good responce from distributing this preview archive but
I wasn't expecting to get so many nice emails. I like to recieve emails whether
they are good or bad but sometimes they are just asking the same questions
and I have to reply with the same answers all the time so here's a list of
some of the ones that come up every time.....

Q1. Will it really be AGA only or will you support GFX cards and ECS Amigas?
Q2. What about serial and/or TCP/IP support?
Q3. I hate lowres, what about other screen modes?

----

Q1. Will it really be AGA only or will you support GFX cards and ECS Amigas?

A1. I will support as many setups as I can although the game itself will need
up to 2Meg of chip ram so it's not an easy task. As for GFX board support, I'll
do all I can although I don't have a GFX board so I don't exactly have a good
knowlege of programming one. I'm certainly not going to leave out GFX board
support unless something big gets in my way. I'll probably give more info on
this in a future update. On the ESC side.... I'll probably do a 64 colour version
when this 256 colour vrsion is complete. I will simply remap all the 256 colour
graphics to work in 64 colour mode... Shouldn't be too dificult :)

Q2. What about serial and/or TCP/IP support?

A2. I'll keep the serial option open while I'm developing the game. It will be
designed as a 1 or 2 player game using a split screen system and a 4 player
(quarter screen) version will not be ruled out just yet. With this in mind, it
shouldn't be too hard to add serial/null modem support. As for a TCP version, I
don't have enough knowlege of TCP programming to rule that out but the
"telser.device" looke interesting and if possible I'll keep the null modem system
open to be compatable with telser.

Q3. I hate lowres, what about other screen modes?

A3. I'll add a screen mode and screen size function so that the game will be able
to play on other screen sizes such as "640x512" "800x400" and the interface
should be able to "scale" to use the new dimensions. You will have to understand
that a screen mode of 640x512 will make the game over 4 times slower but at
least you'll have the choice.

---

I'll add more of the questions next time....

Please don't worry about emailing me with anything other than the above questions.
I'll add any of the interesting ones to the above list.

@EndNode


