@Node Keys "Editor Controls..."

@{u}Keys & Controls@{uu}

If you've already run the program then you'll probably have loaded this up to
find out exactly how to work it!!

Here are the keys...

Esc     = Quit
Cursors = Move about the map.
Del     = Update little Map, takes a few seconds sorry :)
Help    = Save Map with current filename... Do this often!!!
S       = Save but you can also choose a new name.
L       = Load in a diferent map file.
Lalt    = Place current object
LAmiga  = remove object

Numeric Pad :- It's AGA only so you should have a numeric pad??? :)

1      Cursor Left    <- these are a little confusing compared to cursor movement
2      Cursor Down        
3      Cursor Right
5      Cursor Up
0      Center cursor in screen
+      Next Object
Enter  Prev Object


"(" & "7"  = Raise/lower by 1 point
")" & "8"  = Raise/lower by 3 points
"/" & "9"  = Raise/lower by 5 points
"*" & "-"  = Raise/lower by 7 points

F8  = Flatten to current height around by radius 1 < Just try these out
F9  = Flatten to current height around by radius 2
F10 = Flatten to current height around by radius 3       

If you select the small map (Bottom) with the right button it will bring up
a window with a bigger map in it. This is just for show at the moment...

Selecting the little map with the left button will take you to that spot although
you might have already worked that out :)

@EndNode


################################


@Node Bugs "Bug reporting"

@{u}Bugs... god forbid!@{uu}

Please, please don't send me any bug reports for this program. I don't have
time to make the editor 100% perfect and although 90% of what you see is the
actual game code I still don't want to hear any of your problems unless you
simply can't run it and you are keen to help me.

Don't tell me if this happens:-

 1. It GURU's at any time, especialy when you try and load "non map" files :)
 2. The pointer is currupted or funny colours.
 3. It doesn't work in your screen mode.
 4. It runs in a strange fasion.
 
I'd be happy if you didn't report any strange bugs at all. I've only been working
on this for about a month or so and most of that time was spent swaping from one
idea to another. The game will be in development for at least another 6 months so
any bug fixes I do now will probably come back later :)

One problem that affects only the map editor program is Stack size. I've given
the program a stack of 40k for now but if you are raising a *LOT* of land at the
same time the recursive functions of the land raising feature may run out of
stack causing a GURU but it didn't happen often with just 4k stack so it should
be safe.

there isn't much error checking on the map loading/saving so you could easily
crash it if you attempted to load a "non map" file.

@EndNode

