@Node Next "Whats in the next versions"

@{u}The Next versions@{uu}

I'll probably upload a new version of this program every two weeks or so
depending on what nasty bugs were in it and how much I've improoved it.

I'm currently working on some speed up features that will make the scrolling
and screen update about 30% faster. Please don't judge the speed level the way
it is at the moment (It could get slower ;)

It's funny how people comment on my computer being slow 020/14 when I complain
about such things as MUI but once you write a game thats slow on an 020, people
slag you off :)  Don't worry things can only get better!!!

I'll try and get a GameView Demo that will load in your map and show you what it
looks like with some water effects, roads, cows, buildings and some people moving
about. Most of this is already programmed but I haven't got anythign that looks prety
enough for your high standards :)

You'll be able to lower and raise the land with just the mouse buttons.

@EndNode

##################

@Node Game "About the game"

@{u}A little about the game@{uu}

I must tell you now that the game wont be anywhere near completed for at least
6-8 months!!! If it's at a completed stage in the first half of 1997 then I'll
be happy.

The reason why it's not going to be completed for so long is becasue I'm going
to take a nice 3 month long holiday to Brazil to see the nicest person in the whole
wide world and she's an Amiga user as well :) Hi Mariane, if you are reading. For
the next couple of months I'll be working on the basics of the game and getting it
moving in the right direction. I'll be here until mid September so theres plenty of
time for you to get in touch. I might even be able to continue developing the game
while I'm on my holiday because I'm such a a devoted Amigan!!! Who else goes for
a 3 month holiday in the sun and spends some of it developing for the Amiga?

@{u}This is what the game will be like@{uu}

1. It will look very much like Settlers although it will play more like Mega-lo-mania
with a bit of Populous thrown in as well as a big helping of my own ideas and any
good ideas that get thrown my way....

2. It won't be so over complicated as Settlers:-

  No need for toolmakers etc... I'll not use tricky systems but I will have some simple
  buildings that just help the game along such as fishermen, hunters, churches etc...
  All these things will help the game in a certain way such as morale, energy etc...

3. More relaxed mining and food system, not too tricky to use...

4. Much more advanced war aspect.

  Full control over who goes where.
  Most of the game will be based around war strategies.
  I suppose it will play a little bit like "Command & Conquer meets Settlers/Populous"
  although I've only seen C & C a couple of times so I don't really know what I'm
  talking about :) Maybe someone can fill me in on the good bits in C & C so I can
  take ideas from it. What do you like about it?

5. Faster building system similar to Mega-lo-mania.

  The building will be based around a design and build system. Set aside so many people
  to work on a building design and then it gets built. So you could have say a maximum
  of 4 buildings being designed at once, maybe more???

  23 people working on a Mine.
  14 people working on a fishermans hut.
  30 People working on a Guard Tower.

  in order to build two fishermans huts, two fishermans huts need to be designed so
  you will be able to pre-design up to 4 buildings at once, mabe more???

  Once these are designed they will go into a ready to build "pile" and they only
  take a few seconds to be placed down in the game ready to be used. That bit will
  be quite interesting..

  As in mega-lo-mania, the gameplay will have a lot to do with how many people you
  have. The more people you have in your "base" the faster they reproduce and the faster
  you can design buildings. You will also be able to go out and kill your opponents
  innocent people in order to bring his population down. There will be death by natural
  causes as well so you have to look after your people.

6. Plenty of ingame control over the "lay of the land" You will be able to employ
   workers to go out and raise or lower the land in certain areas. As well as this you
   will be able to place TNT anywhere you like in order to blast a hole which will
   clear away plenty of land....

I have many more ideas about most aspects of the game and I'll be happy to discus
any of them with you. It's hard for you/me to see how things will actually work
until they are implimented so I've got a lot of work to do... Some of the above will
change as the game goes on....

Please send your coments and suggestions to me!!!

@EndNode

