@Node MapFormat "The map format...

@{u}The Map format@{uu}

The maps can be given any name you like, they don't have to be map1.map, map2.map
but it's nice to have them end in .map.

I'd like to see some countries recreated with this system such as a nice map of
Iceland or a nice map of Italy. I don't know what I'll do if I get more than one
map of Italy or three maps of Brazil though :)

I will try and keep the file format the same as I go on. If not, I'll make sure
the editor can load in older map formats. The file size for each map is 75k
which will go down with some sort of custom compression routine which should
make it 10-20k or so...

It all depends how much data I allow to be set with the map editor. At the moment
you can only alter the height of the land and you can add some of the simple
objects I've designed already.

@EndNode

